projects.description:
Technical Lead for delivering an upgrade to Stageclip's core video creation and processing service, integrating with Adobe After Effects. This will enable them to improve the quality of their core product, whilst not affecting their parallel migration to a new user platform being developed separately. In this role, I am responsible for:
* Implementing an Agile approach and concepts to manage work and productivity - kanban, sprints, regular cross-team communication, acceptance criteria, user stories;
* Ensuring my team members have the knowledge and support to complete their tasks;
* Gathering requirements, refining the technical specification, and writing tickets;
* Managing the expectations of the Stageclip CTO through regular updates on project progress, risks and actions;
* Working closely with managers and Stageclip’s engineering partner to ensure timely and effective delivery;
* Exploring and developing opportunities for new work;
* Code reviews, mentoring and providing team feedback.

Worked across a range of products to accelerate David Lloyd's digital transformation roadmap. Their plan was split across workstreams to increase new membership, improve retention, increase sales & subscriptions (e.g. to classes and courses) and streamline their internal processes to improve efficiency.

My role included work to:
* Upgrade their public facing website to increase membership sign-ups by providing a modern design and customisable content via a custom-made Content Management System;
* Upgrade their internal booking system to automate manual processes and improving the code base by extracting an old PHP monolith into Java microservices;
* Create a new membership registration app for in-club sales teams to improve the registration process and experience for both staff and prospective members.
